  "prompt": "What will be the PSU cut off for the all categories?",
  "response": "The **PSU (Public Sector Undertakings) cut-off** for different categories (General, OBC, SC, ST, EWS, etc.) varies based on the job role, the PSU conducting the recruitment, and the difficulty level of the position. Here are some general insights into PSU cut-offs:\n\n### **Factors Affecting PSU Cut-Off:**\n1. **Job Role**: Higher-level positions (Engineers, Management Trainees) may have higher cut-offs compared to entry-level roles.\n2. **Number of Vacancies**: Fewer vacancies often lead to higher cut-offs.\n3. **Difficulty of Exam**: A tougher exam usually results in a lower cut-off.\n4. **Number of Applicants**: More applicants can increase competition, raising the cut-off.\n5. **Category**: Reserved categories (SC/ST/OBC/EWS) generally have lower cut-offs than the General category.\n\n---\n\n### **Expected Cut-Off Trends (Approximate):**\nHere\u2019s a rough estimate based on past trends (may vary for specific PSUs):\n\n| **Category** | **Cut-Off Percentage** (Approx.) |\n|--------------|----------------------------------|\n| General      | 90-98%                          |\n| OBC          | 85-92%                          |\n| SC           | 80-88%                          |\n| ST           | 75-85%                          |\n| EWS          | 85-92%                          |\n\n---\n\n### **PSU-Specific Examples:**\n1. **ONGC (Graduate Trainee)**:\n   - General: 85-90%\n   - OBC: 80-85%\n   - SC/ST: 75-80%\n\n2. **BHEL (Engineer Trainee)**:\n   - General: 92-95%\n   - OBC: 88-90%\n   - SC/ST: 82-85%\n\n3. **SAIL (Management Trainee)**:\n   - General: 90-95%\n   - OBC: 85-90%\n   - SC/ST: 80-85%\n\n---\n\n### **How to Check PSU Cut-Off:**\n- Visit the official website of the PSU you applied for.\n- Look for the **cut-off list** or **result notification**.\n- Some PSUs provide category-wise cut-offs in the recruitment notification.\n\n### **Note**: These are **approximate** cut-offs and may vary depending on the specific PSU, year, and vacancies. Always refer to the official notifications for accurate details.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
